1
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:02,200
welcome back everyone

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:05,166
today you should get ready for more craziness

3
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:10,233
since we are going to use a bunch of eyes of harmony to contain multiple universes

4
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:12,866
crafting one of those takes a lot of time

5
00:00:12,866 --> 00:00:17,633
and many machines which we used to tink were already expensive on their own

6
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:22,266
and it will also take some new blocks which are just as much expensive

7
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:27,033
and all of those blocks will recursively contain other expensive stuff

8
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:27,466
also

9
00:00:27,466 --> 00:00:31,066
we need some parts that are rather slow to process

10
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:35,300
even with our extruder powered by 8 UMV energy hatches

11
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,800
thus we shall build more of those

12
00:00:37,866 --> 00:00:41,266
which means we will be needing more energy hatches

13
00:00:41,266 --> 00:00:43,433
and what we now lack off is water

14
00:00:43,766 --> 00:00:46,433
so we have to look into a proper source of water

15
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:49,266
and a kitchen sink doesn't seem to work properly

16
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:49,900
luckily

17
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:52,866
the reservoir hatch seems to work well enough

18
00:00:52,866 --> 00:00:57,033
if we give it enough time to stock up fluid in a second storage

19
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,566
now that we have water

20
00:00:58,566 --> 00:01:01,300
we can start working on fixing the next issue

21
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:02,700
assembly lines

22
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:05,766
our old generic setup has a couple of issues

23
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:07,233
when crafting slow things

24
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,833
new things can queue up

25
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:11,233
and end up having to wait too much time

26
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,533
so we shall expand it

27
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:13,866
but

28
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:17,366
this time we will use advanced assembly lines

29
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:21,566
those will leave some items in the buses locking the usage

30
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:26,666
also those can do parallel crafting when the conditions allow for it

31
00:01:26,766 --> 00:01:31,833
but doing parallel while also allowing for multipurpose crafting has its caveat

32
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:35,433
requiring a more complex setup we may see later on

33
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,066
anyways

34
00:01:36,066 --> 00:01:40,700
we now got to the point of researching the main block of the eye of harmony

35
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,800
which is starting to require a lot of computation

36
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:46,366
and while we get the research done

37
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,066
we can also get the crafting items ready

38
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:51,633
once we got to the point of crafting it

39
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:54,833
we realized that this is going to take too much time

40
00:01:55,066 --> 00:01:56,433
we have no hurry for that

41
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:59,266
but since this is using relatively no power

42
00:01:59,266 --> 00:02:00,700
we can overclock it

43
00:02:00,866 --> 00:02:03,266
don't worry about voiding the crafting

44
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:06,166
since this is an advanced assembly line

45
00:02:06,166 --> 00:02:08,900
we only lost the first item and the fluids

46
00:02:08,966 --> 00:02:12,000
meaning a bunch of space elevators and neutronium

47
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,600
to overclock it

48
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,200
we shall use a laser hatch

49
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:18,300
that can bring half of our total energy production

50
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:21,700
this assembly line is going to work with a single slice

51
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:25,033
so it won't use more than 3 percent of our production

52
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,633
meanwhile we also have a bunch of assembly lines

53
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:31,500
with dedicated recipe for parallelization

54
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:36,033
those are probably going to be working way more often and at full capacity

55
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:39,233
so we throttle them by lowering the amperage

56
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,100
and to get those amounts of power in that place

57
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,000
we will need a better capacitor

58
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:47,300
which we shall place in a dedicated nearby LSC

59
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,266
with that

60
00:02:48,266 --> 00:02:51,033
we can now start crafting things that

61
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:55,800
will use one Dyson sphere of power for 45 seconds over 16 steps

62
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:58,866
meanwhile using 3 Dysons of power

63
00:02:58,866 --> 00:03:01,600
we can quickly craft the other parts

64
00:03:01,966 --> 00:03:04,100
however before getting to that point

65
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,366
we had to fix a couple of things

66
00:03:06,466 --> 00:03:10,466
the last step of the crafting was supposed to be time consuming

67
00:03:10,466 --> 00:03:13,100
but the other steps are resource intensive

68
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,966
and the main issue was our circuit production

69
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:17,833
those things are so clogged

70
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:21,400
that the issue even falls to our crafting network storage

71
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:25,200
thus it is time to increase the size of our circuit factory

72
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:28,066
and that was the first floor of circuit production

73
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:31,766
so we slowly work through each of the floors of our factory

74
00:03:31,866 --> 00:03:36,200
which was overall quite easy thanks to the newly discovered tools

75
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,900
with those new circuits

76
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,666
we can quickly finish up the crafting of our first eye of harmony

77
00:03:41,866 --> 00:03:45,366
and this is one more multi block with special requirements

78
00:03:45,566 --> 00:03:48,566
the first being the need to change our game UI size

79
00:03:48,566 --> 00:03:50,666
to properly see what it does

80
00:03:50,766 --> 00:03:52,766
from a single run of that thing

81
00:03:52,766 --> 00:03:56,200
we are going to get huge amount of every kind of resource

82
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:57,866
but what we care about is

83
00:03:57,866 --> 00:04:00,400
the condensed raw stellar plasma mixture

84
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,800
and white dwarf matter

85
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:02,666
however

86
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:04,600
the recipe time is really high

87
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,000
and takes more inputs than we can input in a single tick

88
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:12,866
so we will probably look into some overclocking for the first few iterations

89
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,566
to help us with that and other future planning

90
00:04:15,566 --> 00:04:19,766
we can use this helpful spreadsheet suggested by the quest book

91
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:24,500
all is left to do is to load up the eye of harmony with the input fluids

92
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,433
which will take some time

93
00:04:26,966 --> 00:04:28,300
once it has enough

94
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:29,600
we can turn it on

95
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,500
however

96
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:33,433
it looks like it's not going to produce anything

97
00:04:33,566 --> 00:04:36,233
and that is because we've fed it too much fluid

98
00:04:36,266 --> 00:04:38,633
and the meaning of that fancy formula is that

99
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:42,600
you get nothing if you insert 5% fluid more than needed

100
00:04:42,766 --> 00:04:45,266
so to insert exact amounts

101
00:04:45,266 --> 00:04:50,433
we shall use a convoluted system that involves ae2 and crafting cards

102
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:53,066
after slowly charging up the machine

103
00:04:53,066 --> 00:04:55,433
we managed to make it run with full output

104
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:58,366
and with a recipe that will finish in less than an hour

105
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:02,900
and that overclock took the power we accumulated in a couple of days

106
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:03,866
anyways

107
00:05:03,866 --> 00:05:06,666
that machine is still in its crude state

108
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,166
we want to upgrade it at least to perfect

109
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:11,766
if we want to produce molten universium

110
00:05:11,766 --> 00:05:14,866
the material used in any UXV part

111
00:05:15,166 --> 00:05:15,600
however

112
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:19,666
getting a perfect eye of harmony requires black dwarf matter

113
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:22,833
which can be obtained from the advanced tier onwards

114
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:23,733
to get those

115
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:26,900
we lack of white dwarf matter and infinity

116
00:05:27,066 --> 00:05:29,500
we have already built a lot of DTPFs

117
00:05:29,966 --> 00:05:32,033
so we shall look for a better way

118
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:36,366
such as upgrading one with a transdimensional alignment matrix

119
00:05:36,366 --> 00:05:41,566
that thing will speed up our Infinity production by 20 times meanwhile

120
00:05:41,566 --> 00:05:44,466
the white dwarf matter has become a major issue

121
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:46,600
our production is already too low

122
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:50,400
and our power production can't even keep up with that little production

123
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,266
to get a better understanding of the situation

124
00:05:53,266 --> 00:05:55,166
we can go back to our spreadsheet

125
00:05:55,166 --> 00:06:00,700
and see how our energy production and objective progress varies in function of overclocks

126
00:06:00,966 --> 00:06:05,200
and getting the tier 4 eye of harmony like that is not going to be okay

127
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,400
to increase the production there are many ways

128
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:12,800
an interesting one is upgrading the time dilation field generators

129
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,900

Thus cutting in four the time required


130
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:17,966
but with a 20% chance of recipe failing

131
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:21,266
the issue is that those will cost white dwarf matter

132
00:06:21,266 --> 00:06:23,166
but a more reasonable amount

133
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:25,366
that will still take some time

134
00:06:25,366 --> 00:06:28,833
which we can use to further upgrade our power production

135
00:06:29,066 --> 00:06:31,366
with all of that time at our disposal

136
00:06:31,366 --> 00:06:34,900
we managed to build more than 100 Dyson Spheres

137
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,766
enough to fill an ultimate battery in three hours

138
00:06:38,066 --> 00:06:41,466
and once we manage to gather enough white dwarf matter

139
00:06:41,466 --> 00:06:45,366
we can upgrade our time dilation field generators to tier 3

140
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:49,200
which will yield around 3 times more than the tier 1

141
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:53,200
and to round up our production to 1 milli-bucket per second

142
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:56,766
we can use the leftover parts on a second eye of harmony

143
00:06:57,033 --> 00:07:01,233
and to avoid having to build a second convoluted gas loading system

144
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:02,900
we have split the complex part

145
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:05,866
in a way that can be shared across multiple machines

146
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,066
anyways as said

147
00:07:08,066 --> 00:07:11,800
we are now producing white dwarf matter 4 times faster

148
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:16,166
but it's still not enough to reach the tier 4 in a reasonable amount of time

149
00:07:16,266 --> 00:07:19,300
tier 4 is required for the black dwarf matter

150
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:22,600
but for a fifth of the cost we can move to tier 3

151
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:24,500
while on the current setup

152
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,500
it doesn't make a huge difference

153
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:29,633
it will allow for usage of tier 3 dimensions

154
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:32,033
which won't make black dwarf matter yet

155
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:35,000
but will make huge amount of white dwarf matter

156
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,566
allowing for faster tier 4 progression

157
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:41,566
so while we wait a couple of hours for the missing materials

158
00:07:41,566 --> 00:07:45,966
we can go and take a trip inside one of our pocket universes we have created

159
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:49,033
where we can admire the creation and destruction of the stars

160
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:51,600
from which we extract the dwarf matter

161
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:54,833
and after exploring multiple microverses

162
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:56,333
we gather enough materials

163
00:07:56,333 --> 00:08:00,766
to increase the tier of our spacetime compression field generators

164
00:08:00,766 --> 00:08:04,766
which means that we can now contain tier 3 dimensions

165
00:08:04,766 --> 00:08:08,066
thus making 4 times the amount of white dwarf matter

166
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,500
the issue now has become our assembly lines again

167
00:08:11,766 --> 00:08:14,366
we are not using those at their full potential

168
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,166
we have some generic ones

169
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:18,600
which are not using the parallel feature

170
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:23,466
and other specific that require to manually set the filters for the recipe they do

171
00:08:23,466 --> 00:08:24,300
however

172
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:27,800
we just noticed a feature that could help us fix all our issues

173
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,466
and make the perfect assembly line setup

174
00:08:30,566 --> 00:08:36,200
a setup that will allow for multi recipe parallel crafting on multiple assembly lines at once

175
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:39,300
explaining how it works doesn't fit in this video

176
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:42,666
but you can just admire here how nicely it works

177
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:47,466
and that is just one of the many assembly lines that will manage slow craftings

178
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,200
we will want more of those

179
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,500
but while making it

180
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:53,900
we already finished the tier 4 eye of harmony

181
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:56,100
this will make black dwarf matter

182
00:08:56,100 --> 00:08:57,833
but with those settings

183
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,766
the production is too low

184
00:08:59,866 --> 00:09:01,833
so we made more eyes of harmony

185
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:05,566
to stock up a lot of white dwarf matter for other upgrades

186
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:09,833

the perfect tier of harmony requires quite some black dwarf matter


187
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,200
so let's see how we can get to it

188
00:09:12,266 --> 00:09:12,900
as of now

189
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:15,800
that would take approximately 100 hours

190
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,800
and on a power loss

191
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:20,433
which we could fix by making a bunch more of Dyson Spheres

192
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:23,400
we could speed up the process by making more tier 4 eyes

193
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:26,833
but then we would probably have to lower the overclock setting

194
00:09:26,966 --> 00:09:30,233
the best option is probably to do one step at a time

195
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,866
thus working on a tier 5 eye of harmony

196
00:09:33,066 --> 00:09:35,100
which will allow for a faster tier 6

197
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,433
at that point

198
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:39,700
we notice that our success rate is getting too low

199
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:42,600
we can trade some yield to increase it

200
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,933
and once we have the tier 6

201
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:47,600
we will be able to work on the tier 7

202
00:09:47,766 --> 00:09:51,066
but we will probably want to first make a bunch more of tier 6

203
00:09:51,066 --> 00:09:53,000
and lower the overclocking

204
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:54,566
and of course

205
00:09:54,566 --> 00:09:56,700
mass producing those machines like that

206
00:09:56,700 --> 00:10:00,100
started to be heavy for our experimental assembly line

207
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,166
so we had to add a bunch more

208
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:04,566
which we are now connecting wirelessly

209
00:10:04,633 --> 00:10:05,700
and with that

210
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,966
we now have a bunch of eyes

211
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,233
which finally managed to produce some universium

212
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,266
to use it

213
00:10:12,266 --> 00:10:14,866
we shall start by solidifying it into ingots

214
00:10:14,866 --> 00:10:17,200
which we then extrude into blocks

215
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:17,966
with those

216
00:10:17,966 --> 00:10:20,633
we can now make universium nanites

217
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,433
which have many usages

218
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:24,466
but the main one is going to be making

219
00:10:24,466 --> 00:10:27,766
magnetohydrodynamically constrained star matter

220
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:32,466
which is used in all of the parts and components of the next and last tier

221
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:36,900
but there are still a couple of materials we still don't have access to

222
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:38,900
the first one is eternity

223
00:10:39,433 --> 00:10:40,633
to get that stuff

224
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:43,566
we start by acquiring some time pieces

225
00:10:43,766 --> 00:10:46,233
then we add a group of Universium Nanites

226
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,966
to get the Temporal Harmonizer Catalyst

227
00:10:49,166 --> 00:10:51,600
this will allow us to produce eternity

228
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:54,466
but it will use some chronic singularities

229
00:10:54,466 --> 00:10:57,800
which we will be able to make easily using some eternity

230
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,900
but for the first iteration

231
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,566
we have to go with the more expensive way

232
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:02,966
also

233
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:06,200
to get more eternity out of our recipe loop

234
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:09,200
we can add some fermium and neptunium plasma

235
00:11:09,466 --> 00:11:12,833
the other main ingredient for the next tier is magmatter

236
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:17,766
this stuff is produced in the heliofusion excisiter Gorge module

237
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,533
however

238
00:11:18,533 --> 00:11:21,766
making it is not as easy as it might seems

239
00:11:21,866 --> 00:11:22,800
to begin with

240
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:25,833
we have to unlock the last upgrade of the forge

241
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,233
and that is going to take a lot of Graviton Shards

242
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:33,633
which means we have to use our forge more to reach more milestones

243
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:37,033
an easy want to do is to process some more stuff

244
00:11:37,066 --> 00:11:40,166
since we have different issues doing it as a single step

245
00:11:40,166 --> 00:11:43,066
we shall split the task to multiple CPUs

246
00:11:43,066 --> 00:11:44,266
and it turns out that

247
00:11:44,266 --> 00:11:48,700
making a quarter of integer 32 steel ingots took a single tick

248
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:51,000
we repeat the process a bunch of times

249
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,633
to get our new shards

250
00:11:52,633 --> 00:11:55,200
however those didn't get us far

251
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:58,600
so we retrieve some from unneeded upgrades

252
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:01,466
then after making one more upgrade

253
00:12:01,466 --> 00:12:04,800
which also took all of our really ultimate batteries

254
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,000
we again run out of shards

255
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,400
luckily

256
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,300
there is a weird looping recipe

257
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:12,566
that can make us easily melt overflowing amount of stuff

258
00:12:12,566 --> 00:12:13,033
however

259
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:15,866
we now maxed out the conversion milestone

260
00:12:15,866 --> 00:12:17,966
and need to do something else

261
00:12:17,966 --> 00:12:20,066
like heating up some nitrogen

262
00:12:20,066 --> 00:12:23,500
heating it up to plasma uses quite a lot of power

263
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,800
thus helping us reach the next charge milestone

264
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:27,533
with that

265
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:30,300
we are now in front of the last upgrade

266
00:12:30,433 --> 00:12:34,066
the main issue here is the crazy amount of batteries we need

267
00:12:34,066 --> 00:12:35,100
currently

268
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:39,166
the only thing we lack of to craft those is some heavy radox

269
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,900
but let's get things more in perspective

270
00:12:41,966 --> 00:12:45,166
crafting those batteries is a recursive process

271
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:48,700
meaning that the situation gets exponentially worse

272
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:49,133
luckily

273
00:12:49,133 --> 00:12:51,966
we unlocked a better way of making batteries

274
00:12:51,966 --> 00:12:53,800
that hugely cut the cost

275
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:54,500
however

276
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:58,700
that still used up the same amount of components that heavily use naquadria

277
00:12:58,700 --> 00:13:00,833
since we couldn't produce enough

278
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:04,000
we have been integrating with some heavy radox

279
00:13:04,066 --> 00:13:06,033
we could increase its production

280
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:08,900
but there is a better way of solving this issue

281
00:13:08,966 --> 00:13:10,966
we can do an even higher skip

282
00:13:10,966 --> 00:13:14,066
by using some of the newly acquired materials

283
00:13:14,066 --> 00:13:16,833
but that is going to take quite some universium

284
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,833
so we better keep an eye on that

285
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,800
or maybe even more than one

286
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,900
actually let's be specific

287
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:26,700
to get the 10 million universium required in less than a day

288
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:30,066
we'd need 100 maxed out eyes of harmony

289
00:13:30,166 --> 00:13:31,666
so for the moment

290
00:13:31,666 --> 00:13:34,700
we better off find a better way of making Naquadria

291
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:37,666
increasing our ore or collection is the main way

292
00:13:37,666 --> 00:13:39,800
but there's something else we can do

293
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:43,766
by adding some catalysts to our quantum force transformer

294
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,366
we can increase the output

295
00:13:45,366 --> 00:13:49,400
and also focus more of the outputs to the one we care about

296
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:53,866
and that was the only thing we lacked of to craft the required batteries

297
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,966
then we spent some time AFK

298
00:13:55,966 --> 00:13:58,666
to unlock the next catalyst milestone

299
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:01,266
so that we have enough shards to complete the path

300
00:14:01,266 --> 00:14:03,966
that will allow us to process mag matter

301
00:14:04,166 --> 00:14:07,433
however producing such materials is not as easy

302
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:10,066
as throwing random stuff in a machine

303
00:14:10,366 --> 00:14:14,100
after getting an heliofusion exotizer in magmatter mode

304
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:16,266
we have to complete its mini game

305
00:14:16,466 --> 00:14:17,100
once started

306
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:21,200
this machine will give us a tiny pile of some expensive materials

307
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:24,366
followed by some drops of space time products

308
00:14:24,633 --> 00:14:25,833
to get magmatter

309
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:32,500
we have to send back the difference between the two fluids as ingots of the material of the tiny dust in plasma form

310
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:37,066
so we quickly improvise a way of quickly getting the needed plasma

311
00:14:37,066 --> 00:14:39,033

and give it back to the exoticizer


312
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:41,800
with also the other two fluids it gave us

313
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:42,866
and with that

314
00:14:42,866 --> 00:14:45,700
we have finally obtained our first magmatter

315
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:49,700
the issue now is finding a way of automating that process

316
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:50,666
and maybe

317
00:14:50,666 --> 00:14:54,766
that actually is as easy as throwing random stuff at a new machine

318
00:14:55,033 --> 00:14:56,700
all we have to do is make sure

319
00:14:56,700 --> 00:15:01,000
it always has any of the 14 different plasmas at its disposal

320
00:15:01,266 --> 00:15:03,566
and we can loop back the other two fluids

321
00:15:03,566 --> 00:15:06,866
since we won't be doing any math with that setup

322
00:15:07,433 --> 00:15:08,900
now that we have magmater

323
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,266
we can finally work on the UXV components

324
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,266
and I got to say

325
00:15:14,266 --> 00:15:16,200
this is a really sophisticated motor

326
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:20,433
since not only it contains wetware mainframes in some of its winding

327
00:15:20,433 --> 00:15:26,100
it also contains ultra high tier electrical circuitry inside the balls of its bearings

328
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:26,600
anyways

329
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:29,966
after quickly researching UXV energy hatches

330
00:15:29,966 --> 00:15:32,400
we upgrade our implosion compressor

331
00:15:32,633 --> 00:15:35,400
this will allow us to unlock all the recipes

332
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,566
such as the one that will cut in half the universium cost

333
00:15:38,566 --> 00:15:42,866
when making magnetohydrodynamically constrained star matter

334
00:15:43,133 --> 00:15:46,200
then to further reduce material usage

335
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:49,200
we will want a UXV component assembly line

336
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:53,300
but we are quickly reminded that our universium production is quite low

337
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:57,200
so we start crafting our first max out eye of harmony

338
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,766
all made out of gallifreyan parts

339
00:15:59,766 --> 00:16:01,466
that thing is now so powerful

340
00:16:01,466 --> 00:16:04,833
that it can contain one whole  solar system

341
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:09,700
and not only will it give off huge amounts of any raw material present in the game

342
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,966
it will also produce more energy than it uses

343
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,166
and to load it at a decent speed

344
00:16:15,166 --> 00:16:18,400
we now have access to the humongous input hatch

345
00:16:18,466 --> 00:16:23,900
but that thing still produces only 1.6 liters of universium per second

346
00:16:23,933 --> 00:16:27,200
and to get just one UXV component assembly line

347
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:30,400
we need 27 millions of liters of that stuff

348
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:33,866
it doesn't take much to understand that we are going nowhere

349
00:16:33,866 --> 00:16:37,066
even if we were to spam more of those machines

350
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:41,000
so we have to research for something even better than the best tier

351
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:44,366
and we came up with one quite interesting solution

352
00:16:44,366 --> 00:16:46,400
the astral fabricator array

353
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:50,966
those things are meant to be inserted inside an eye of harmony to add parallelism

354
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,866
with some downsides

355
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,966
the first one we notice is that

356
00:16:54,966 --> 00:16:57,100
the power output goes negative

357
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:01,100
but working in that mode will consume raw stellar plasma mixture

358
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,966
and we will be going negative on that stuff too

359
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:07,366
that is caused mostly by the low success rate

360
00:17:07,366 --> 00:17:10,666
but we can downgrade one time dilatation field generator

361
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:12,900
to go back to positive production

362
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:15,466
now it is just a matter of figuring out

363
00:17:15,466 --> 00:17:19,666
how many astral array we will need to get a good enough source of universium

364
00:17:19,866 --> 00:17:22,633
and how to keep up with the power consumption

365
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:23,666
anyways

366
00:17:23,666 --> 00:17:27,200
since our old setup isn't making enough materials

367
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,566
we tear it down so that we can recycle it

368
00:17:29,566 --> 00:17:31,566
to make our first astral array

369
00:17:31,766 --> 00:17:32,833
and that thing alone

370
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:35,300
with an almost maxed out eye of harmony

371
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:39,833
is already going to make 5 times as much as our old maxed out eye

372
00:17:39,966 --> 00:17:41,900
but that is still not enough

373
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:46,033
thus we started the mass production of Astral Array fabricators

374
00:17:46,033 --> 00:17:47,300
and with that

375
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:51,066
we are now exponentially increasing our universium production

376
00:17:51,166 --> 00:17:54,600
or at least we were until our batteries run dry

377
00:17:54,666 --> 00:17:59,933
but we managed to complete our UXV component assembly line just in time

378
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:00,966
as usual

379
00:18:00,966 --> 00:18:05,200
this machine will make us use way less materials for each component

380
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:09,566
this time we even skip the compressing of the materials

381
00:18:09,766 --> 00:18:12,866
but we still have to insert part of the circuits

382
00:18:13,033 --> 00:18:13,533
anyways

383
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:16,900
now that we have completed all of the UXV stuff

384
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,700
and unlocked everything in the pack

385
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:21,666
there is only one last challenge left for us

386
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:25,600
but I think that's something we can do in the next episode

387
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:26,966
and the lesson today

388
00:18:26,966 --> 00:18:29,766
is to always keep the coolest stuff hidden

389
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:33,166
so we can have an even greater last episode

390
00:18:33,466 --> 00:18:34,400
bye bye

391
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:02,200
欢迎回来

392
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:05,166
今天可要准备好“疯狂”连击

393
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:10,233

因为我们要用一些鸿蒙之眼来收容多重宇宙


394
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:12,866
做一个EoH就需要大量时间

395
00:00:12,866 --> 00:00:17,633
用于制造它的机器已经足够昂贵了

396
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:22,266
它还需要一些同样昂贵的新方块

397
00:00:22,633 --> 00:00:27,033
所有这些方块都包含其他昂贵的东西

398
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:27,466
而且

399
00:00:27,466 --> 00:00:31,066
我们需要一些加工速度相当慢的零件

400
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:35,300
即使是有八个UMV能源仓的压模机也不行

401
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:37,800
所以得上数量了

402
00:00:37,866 --> 00:00:41,266
也就是说我们需要更多的能量仓

403
00:00:41,266 --> 00:00:43,433
我们现在缺少的是水

404
00:00:43,766 --> 00:00:46,433
所以我们必须寻找合适的水源

405
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:49,266
厨房水槽似乎不能正常工作

406
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:49,900
幸运地

407
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:52,866
蓄水仓工作良好

408
00:00:52,866 --> 00:00:57,033
只要我们给它足够的时间在子网储备液体

409
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,566
现在我们有水了

410
00:00:58,566 --> 00:01:01,300
我们可以开始解决下一个问题

411
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:02,700
装配线

412
00:01:02,833 --> 00:01:05,766
我们旧的通用设置有几个问题

413
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:07,233
在制作缓慢的东西时

414
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,833
新材料会排队

415
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:11,233
最终会浪费大量时间在等待上

416
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,533
所以我们将扩展它

417
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:13,866
但是

418
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:17,366
这次我们将使用进阶装配线

419
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:21,566
它将会在仓室中进行锁定合成

420
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:26,666
条件允许的时候也可以并行合成

421
00:01:26,766 --> 00:01:29,866
但是在对通用装配线进行并行处理时

422
00:01:29,866 --> 00:01:31,833
有值得需要注意的地方

423
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:35,433
稍后便可以看到所需的复杂设置

424
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,066
不管怎样

425
00:01:36,066 --> 00:01:40,700
我们现在要研究鸿蒙之眼的控制方块

426
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,800
这需要大量的算力

427
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:46,366
在我们完成研究的同时

428
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,066
我们也可以准备好材料

429
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:51,633
一旦开始准备制作

430
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:54,833
我们意识到这需要太多时间

431
00:01:55,066 --> 00:01:56,433
我们不着急

432
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:59,266
但由于它相对来说不需要能量

433
00:01:59,266 --> 00:02:00,700
我们可以超频

434
00:02:00,866 --> 00:02:03,266

不用担心材料被吞


435
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:06,166
因为它是进阶装配线

436
00:02:06,166 --> 00:02:08,900

我们只丢失了第一个流体和第一个物品


437
00:02:08,966 --> 00:02:12,000
也就是一堆太空电梯和中子

438
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,600
要超频它

439
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,200
我们将使用激光仓

440
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:18,300
灌入基地一半的发电量

441
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:21,700
这条装配线将进行单片工作

442
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:25,033
所以它的消耗不会超过3%的总发电

443
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,633
同时我们还有一堆装配线

444
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:31,500

运行特定的配方来实现并行


445
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:36,033
这些可能会更频繁地满负荷工作

446
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:39,233

所以我们通过限制电流来省电


447
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,100
为了在那儿缓存如此大的能量

448
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:44,000
我们需要一个更好的电容器

449
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:47,300
我们将把它放在附近的LSC中

450
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,266
有了那个

451
00:02:48,266 --> 00:02:51,033
我们现在可以开始制作一个

452
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:55,800
使用一个戴森球的电量、在16步、45秒内完成制作的EoH

453
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:58,866
再使用3个戴森球的电量

454
00:02:58,866 --> 00:03:01,600
我们可以快速制作其他部分

455
00:03:01,966 --> 00:03:04,100
然而，在做完这些东西之前

456
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,366
我们得解决一些事情

457
00:03:06,466 --> 00:03:10,466
制作的最后一步应该很耗时

458
00:03:10,466 --> 00:03:13,100
但其他步骤需要大量材料

459
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,966
主要问题是我们的电路生产

460
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:17,833

材料造成了堵塞


461
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:21,400

导致子网的储存量成了问题


462
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:25,200
因此是时候扩大电路厂的规模了

463
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:28,066
那是电路厂的第一层

464
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:31,766
我们慢慢地建好工厂每一层

465
00:03:31,866 --> 00:03:36,200
由于新发现的工具，这总体上很容易

466
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,900
有了这些新电路

467
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,666
我们很快完成第一个EoH的制作

468
00:03:41,866 --> 00:03:45,366
这是又一个有特殊要求的多方块

469
00:03:45,566 --> 00:03:48,566
首先是需要改变游戏UI大小

470
00:03:48,566 --> 00:03:50,666
来完整地看到它的用途

471
00:03:50,766 --> 00:03:52,766
它每完成一次运行

472
00:03:52,766 --> 00:03:56,200
我们将获得大量资源

473
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:57,866
但我们关心的是

474
00:03:57,866 --> 00:04:00,400
浓缩的原始恒星等离子体混合物

475
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,800
和白矮星物质

476
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:02,666
然而

477
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:04,600
配方耗时实在太高了

478
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,000
总需求输入比我们每tick能输入的都多

479
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:12,866
所以我们可能会在最初的几次迭代中研究一些超频

480
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,566
为了帮助我们在这方面进行一些规划

481
00:04:15,566 --> 00:04:19,766
任务书里这个电子表格可帮上大忙了

482
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:24,500
剩下要做的就是为鸿蒙之眼输入液体

483
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,433
这需要一些时间

484
00:04:26,966 --> 00:04:28,300
一旦原材料足够

485
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:29,600
便可以将其开机

486
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,500
然而

487
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:33,433
看起来它不会产生任何东西

488
00:04:33,566 --> 00:04:36,233
那是因为我们给它灌了太多的液体

489
00:04:36,266 --> 00:04:38,633
这个奇特公式的意思是

490
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:42,600

如果你输入超过需求5%的液体，就不会有产物


491
00:04:42,766 --> 00:04:45,266
所以要输入精确的数目

492
00:04:45,266 --> 00:04:50,433
我们将使用涉及ae2和合成卡的复杂系统

493
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:53,066
慢慢给机器充电后

494
00:04:53,066 --> 00:04:55,433
我们设法让它以完整的输出运行

495
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:58,366
还有一个不到一小时就能完成的配方

496
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:02,900
超频消耗了我们几天积累的能量

497
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:03,866
不管怎样

498
00:05:03,866 --> 00:05:06,666
那台机器仍处于原始状态

499
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,166
我们想至少升级到完美

500
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:11,766
如果我们想制造熔融宇宙素

501
00:05:11,766 --> 00:05:14,866

一种用于任何UXV部件的材料


502
00:05:15,166 --> 00:05:15,600
然而

503
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:19,666
获得完美的鸿蒙之眼需要黑矮星物质

504
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:22,833

需要在先进及更高等级的配方中获得


505
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:23,733
想得到它们

506
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:26,900
我们缺少白矮星物质和无尽

507
00:05:27,066 --> 00:05:29,500
DTPF已经足够多了

508
00:05:29,966 --> 00:05:32,033
所以我们应该寻找更好的方法

509
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:36,366

